quran[9]{c,v,t}:
  34,23,"And no recommendation will be of benefit with Him, except of him whom He will permit. At that point, when horror will be removed from their hearts, they will say, “What did your Fosterer say?” They will say, “The truth.” And He is the High, the Great"
  34,24,"Say, “ Who provides you from the skies and the earth?” Say, “Allah, and certainly (either) we or you are on guidance or in clear error.”"
  34,25,"Say, “You will not question about our crimes neither will we be questioned about what you do.”"
  34,26,"Say, “Our Fosterer will gather us together then He will Judge between us with truth, and He is the judge, the Knowing.”"
  34,27,"Say, “Show me those whom you have joined with Him as partners, by no means (are they partners), no it is Allah (Who is), the Mighty, the Wise.”"
  34,28,"And We have sent you as a conveyer of good news and a warner to all mankind, but the majority of human beings does not know"
  34,29,"And they say, “When will this promise (be fulfilled) if you are truthful?”"
  34,30,"Say, “For you is a promised day which you cannot postpone from its (appointed) time nor can you advance (it).”"
  34,31,"And those who do not believe say, “We will never believe in this Quran nor in (those books) which were before it.” And if you could see when the unjust will be made to stand before their Fosterer, one turning to the other in argument. Those who were considered weak will say to those who were considered great, “Had it not been for you, we would have been believers.”"